WEBVTT

00:00:00.920 --> 00:00:03.230
Well, good evening, everybody. Thank you

00:00:03.240 --> 00:00:06.310
for joining us again tonight. We're

00:00:06.320 --> 00:00:07.830
going to go over just what the Lord

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:10.830
showed us this last time

00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:13.590
and the heaviness of that video.

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:15.670
I prayed over it most of the night last

00:00:15.680 --> 00:00:17.710
night, and

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:20.750
we'll continue to pray over it today

00:00:20.760 --> 00:00:23.230
and for what the Lord has given us

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:25.030
with our new assignments of praying

00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:26.590
for America, praying for President

00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:29.710
Trump, and continuing to lift our nation

00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:32.030
up, lifting up other nations, lifting up

00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:34.310
Canada, and

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:37.030
so on and so on. It seems like it's a

00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:38.830
never-ending deal here.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:41.470
But you know, God has chosen us for

00:00:41.480 --> 00:00:43.190
such a time as this. And isn't it

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.710
wonderful that we have said yes?

00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:47.830
I'm glad to be here. I don't

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:49.110
know about y'all; I guess you are

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:52.390
because you're here. But

00:00:52.400 --> 00:00:54.790
people wanted to know about the book

00:00:54.800 --> 00:00:56.870
that Diana was reading from last night

00:00:56.870 --> 00:00:56.880
because

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:59.070
she didn't say. She goes, "You know,

00:00:59.070 --> 00:00:59.080
Braden,

00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:00.950
I didn't even say which book I

00:01:00.950 --> 00:01:00.960
was."No,

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:02.190
she

00:01:02.200 --> 00:01:03.430
did

00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:05.110
at the

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:07.550
very end.

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:10.070
So I wanted to show you real quick. I

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:11.750
won't make the broadcast real long

00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:13.270
tonight. I'm trying to keep it shorter

00:01:13.270 --> 00:01:13.280
because

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.430
last night was almost three hours.

00:01:15.440 --> 00:01:17.190
I know you all have other things

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.430
to do than just sitting here with me.

00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:23.030
But we'll just cover things real

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:25.190
quick, and then we'll pray and we're

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:27.230
just going to lift up the nation.

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.430
This is the book. Let me hold

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:32.750
it up here real quick.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:36.670
Can they see it

00:01:36.670 --> 00:01:36.680
well?

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:40.510
That's the book that she's reading.

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:41.990
And when she was reading it last night,

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:44.470
this is

00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:45.910
who she was reading.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:47.670
And it's this man right here. Can you

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:50.430
see that?

00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:53.430
We found it—somebody gave it to us

00:01:53.430 --> 00:01:53.440
or

00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:55.510
told us about it in an email. I don't

00:01:55.520 --> 00:01:58.710
know if it was him or whatever, but

00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:01.030
everybody that I know now is reading

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:04.510
this book, especially prayer people.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:05.950
Pastor Kenneth and them are all reading

00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:08.749
it. They said they love it. I

00:02:08.759 --> 00:02:10.790
think it's great. There are other people

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.030
asking about it and wanting to know. Let

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:14.190
me have it one more time so you can see

00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:15.990
it. Is it good? Do

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.830
they have a good photo of

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:20.230
it? Yeah,

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:24.110
so you can see it. You can order it

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:26.910
if you feel led to get it. I don't

00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:30.190
sell books; I don't try to push books. I

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:32.710
have people send me books from all over

00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:35.030
the place—self-published books, major

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:37.030
book writers, all kinds of people trying to get

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:40.150
me to promote their stuff on my channel

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:42.830
so that they can sell their book

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:45.870
and make money. I'm only led

00:02:45.880 --> 00:02:48.310
whenever the Lord leads us to read

00:02:48.320 --> 00:02:51.110
something.

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:53.630
Diana looks at all of it,

00:02:53.640 --> 00:02:55.030
and when we're led by the Spirit of the

00:02:55.040 --> 00:02:56.510
Lord to mention it, it's because it's something that

00:02:56.520 --> 00:02:59.630
we believe we will use and

00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:02.510
apply to our own lives. Diana and I even

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.750
told Pastor Kenneth last

00:03:04.750 --> 00:03:04.760
night,

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:06.670
"This is something that

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:08.270
I will want to read for the rest of my

00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:10.550
life, maybe once a month, once every

00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:13.070
quarter, whatever,"and really try to

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:15.830
refresh yourself on what you're feeding on

00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:18.270
spiritually with the Word

00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:20.670
and supplements of how to

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.990
keep yourself stirred up

00:03:22.990 --> 00:03:23.000
and

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.310
in that champion mindset.

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:31.270
I've

00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:31.280
noticed—and

00:03:31.280 --> 00:03:32.670
a lot of people,

00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:35.470
I say it like

00:03:35.470 --> 00:03:35.480
this—with

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:38.150
the gift that

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.550
God has given me, Brandon doesn't

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:42.150
control it,

00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:44.070
but I'm allowed to see a lot of things

00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:45.630
that people don't

00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:48.110
realize that I'm seeing.

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:50.750
And I know, and I know, and I know. Let me ensure that the focus

00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:50.760
thing is set because

00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:52.150
I don't want

00:03:52.160 --> 00:03:54.030
to be disturbed here.

00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:59.190
I don't want to be a parrot.

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:01.110
I noticed, just like whenever I

00:04:01.110 --> 00:04:01.120
study

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:03.030
Kathryn Kuhlman

00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:05.710
a lot and being around Billy Burke

00:04:05.720 --> 00:04:08.150
and seeing his ministry and how he

00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:10.550
stands alone.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:12.710
He doesn't have a lot of people in

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:15.270
his circle. He's always by himself. He's

00:04:15.280 --> 00:04:18.550
very to himself, very protective

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:21.949
over the anointing that is on his life.

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:24.310
He doesn't allow people really in his

00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:26.950
inner circle. And neither did Sister

00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:28.230
Kuhlman.

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:32.630
There is a pioneer work,

00:04:32.640 --> 00:04:34.790
as I keep learning about

00:04:34.790 --> 00:04:34.800
all—I'm

00:04:34.800 --> 00:04:36.150
new to

00:04:36.160 --> 00:04:37.470
all this

00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:39.670
and I'm learning so much from

00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:42.510
the elders and stuff.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:46.030
It's really easy to be in the place

00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:47.790
of going, "Oh, we don't touch your

00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:50.550
glory, Lord,"and you say certain things

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:55.670
until you're in a position to touch it.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:57.950
You can parrot a lot of things until the glory

00:04:57.950 --> 00:04:57.960
is

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:02.070
on you and pressure comes.

00:05:02.080 --> 00:05:06.870
Flesh always wants to be praised.

00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:08.750
Regardless of who you are, you always

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:12.070
want that 'atta boy'or whatever. But I

00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:13.550
realized that's what

00:05:13.560 --> 00:05:15.950
Satan was wanting. His

00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:18.830
whole mission of operation, his M.O.,

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:21.910
was to be glorified. He

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:24.390
wanted what God got.

00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:27.430
He wanted to exalt his kingdom. He

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:30.510
wanted to be the Most High. "I will

00:05:30.520 --> 00:05:32.150
be bigger than Him; I'll do

00:05:32.150 --> 00:05:32.160
this."So,

00:05:32.160 --> 00:05:33.950
whenever you see people and

00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:35.870
they parrot things and they say they

00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:38.350
want end-time glory, they want the

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:40.510
revival, they want these

00:05:40.510 --> 00:05:40.520
things—I

00:05:40.520 --> 00:05:42.110
watch, and the Lord allows me to see

00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:43.350
it. There

00:05:43.350 --> 00:05:43.360
are

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:45.790
so many people that parrot and

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:48.550
say they want something that they have

00:05:48.560 --> 00:05:51.150
no heart for at all.

00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:54.310
Fruit always displays

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:56.950
what your root truly is.

00:05:56.960 --> 00:05:59.390
And I watch a lot of people because to

00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:02.550
have a revival like John Kilpatrick did

00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:05.750
at Pensacola back in the '90s,

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:08.510
that takes some effort

00:06:08.520 --> 00:06:10.190
beyond anything that anybody will ever

00:06:10.200 --> 00:06:11.630
comprehend.

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:14.710
To have a meeting every single

00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:14.720
day—I

00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:16.110
don't even know when they had

00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:17.710
off, or if they ever had off,

00:06:17.720 --> 00:06:19.310
like Sundays or whatever.

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:21.190
Probably not Sundays, but if they

00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:22.950
had an off day,

00:06:22.960 --> 00:06:25.270
they had to have some rest or they

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:28.030
alternated people out.

00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:30.230
But to really

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:33.910
have revival in your church

00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:36.550
and say, "Listen, we're sold out. We're

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:38.150
going to have church in here 24 hours a

00:06:38.160 --> 00:06:40.310
day, seven days a week. We're going to have

00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:43.070
revival up in this

00:06:43.070 --> 00:06:43.080
place,"and

00:06:43.080 --> 00:06:44.910
not just have these little

00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:44.920
four-day

00:06:44.920 --> 00:06:46.950
tent meeting revivals

00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:46.960
where

00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:48.630
you go,

00:06:48.630 --> 00:06:48.640
"Wahoo,

00:06:48.640 --> 00:06:51.590
we had

00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:52.950
revival,"and

00:06:52.960 --> 00:06:53.430
you're kidding

00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:54.670
yourself.

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:56.190
That's not revival.

00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:57.750
You had a four-day meeting and you're

00:06:57.760 --> 00:06:59.750
calling it revival.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:01.950
When the Lord says, "I'm bringing

00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:04.390
revival to the nation; I'm going to

00:07:04.400 --> 00:07:06.870
bring a revival to these places,"when I

00:07:06.880 --> 00:07:10.030
told you I saw Minnesota

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:11.790
and he said, "I want to do it in

00:07:11.800 --> 00:07:14.190
Tennessee and I have Mobile, Alabama again,

00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:17.190
and I want to use John Kilpatrick again,

00:07:17.200 --> 00:07:19.110
and I'm going to use these

00:07:19.110 --> 00:07:19.120
generals"—well,

00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:21.790
why? Because they are

00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:23.950
sold out. They know what it takes. And

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:26.470
the Lord has me praying for

00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:28.670
these individuals, these men, to be

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:31.310
strong like Moses, that their blood will

00:07:31.320 --> 00:07:32.910
be good, that they will

00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:34.950
make it to the end,

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:37.590
live long, and finish strong. But you have a

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:40.110
lot of people that have been raised

00:07:40.110 --> 00:07:40.120
'churched,'as

00:07:40.120 --> 00:07:42.590
I want to call them. There

00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:42.600
are

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:44.790
a lot of churched people that

00:07:44.800 --> 00:07:47.510
say a lot and say, "Oh, we want

00:07:47.510 --> 00:07:47.520
this,"but

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:49.550
your heart

00:07:49.560 --> 00:07:51.790
never displays it

00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:54.230
by the fruit.

00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:55.910
Does that make sense?

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:57.750
You can say a lot, but you're

00:07:57.760 --> 00:08:00.150
not acting it. You don't

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:02.990
try to implement what you believe.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.990
You can say a lot of things and say, "We

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:06.710
want to grow a ministry."Diana said

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:08.630
one of the major classes I took in

00:08:08.640 --> 00:08:13.110
church growth and

00:08:13.110 --> 00:08:13.120
planting—they

00:08:13.120 --> 00:08:15.510
always teach you that the first

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:15.520
five

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:18.910
years of your ministry really determines

00:08:18.920 --> 00:08:21.670
the whole outcome for the rest of it.

00:08:21.680 --> 00:08:23.830
It's like Joel Osteen. Let me say it

00:08:23.840 --> 00:08:25.350
like this:

00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:27.470
Joel Osteen has the largest church in

00:08:27.480 --> 00:08:29.910
America.

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:34.550
But as he got there, it plateaued.

00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:37.510
Where did it go any higher?

00:08:37.510 --> 00:08:37.520
What

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:40.070
was the cutoff point

00:08:40.080 --> 00:08:41.670
with the church and how many people

00:08:41.680 --> 00:08:44.190
started to attend there? Is he still

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:45.910
growing?

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:48.150
Does he have multiple services every

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:50.390
single week and it's bigger than Dr.

00:08:50.400 --> 00:08:53.510
Cho's church was in South Korea?

00:08:53.520 --> 00:08:56.950
There's a point of a climax

00:08:56.960 --> 00:08:58.590
and it stops

00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:02.190
in ministry. As I'm observing

00:09:02.190 --> 00:09:02.200
and

00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:04.710
watching other ministers,

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:06.310
they

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:07.470
say, "Well, we've been in

00:09:07.480 --> 00:09:10.110
ministry for 30 years, 20 years, 50

00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:10.120
years,"and

00:09:10.120 --> 00:09:11.830
all this stuff, and you see it,

00:09:11.840 --> 00:09:14.750
but their ministry is still the same.

00:09:14.760 --> 00:09:18.670
They hit the plateau of where they are

00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:20.590
and they really have not gone

00:09:20.600 --> 00:09:22.550
anywhere year

00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:24.790
after year. And you watch certain

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:27.230
things, but they talk about the revival.

00:09:27.240 --> 00:09:28.910
They talk about this and

00:09:28.910 --> 00:09:28.920
that.

00:09:28.920 --> 00:09:30.910
As a young

00:09:30.920 --> 00:09:32.390
student,

00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:35.190
I watch

00:09:35.190 --> 00:09:35.200
and

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:36.630
ask,

00:09:36.640 --> 00:09:40.590
"How do I implement what

00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:42.630
I'm learning?"because I'm just starting

00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:44.790
out and learning from

00:09:44.790 --> 00:09:44.800
many

00:09:44.800 --> 00:09:46.910
people. I watch big

00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:48.710
ministries all around now, and I am

00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:51.110
privy to a lot of conversations

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:53.350
that I never was before. But I

00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:55.830
don't want to be a parrot; that's what I'm

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:57.710
trying to say. When you are a

00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:59.630
groundbreaker

00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:01.190
into something that has never been done

00:10:01.190 --> 00:10:01.200
before—Kathryn

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:03.430
Kuhlman was persecuted.

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.790
They said she was a witch.

00:10:05.800 --> 00:10:07.790
They said she's a woman and she can't be

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:10.270
used of God because she is a woman.

00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:13.150
"You can't use a

00:10:13.150 --> 00:10:13.160
woman."And

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:14.990
Kathryn Kuhlman was a woman. She went

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:17.590
through so much to get where she

00:10:17.590 --> 00:10:17.600
was—most

00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:19.870
people would never

00:10:19.880 --> 00:10:21.710
have been

00:10:21.710 --> 00:10:21.720
there—but

00:10:21.720 --> 00:10:24.510
she was sold out, and it was real. This

00:10:24.510 --> 00:10:24.520
is

00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:27.350
versus somebody who's in ministry that

00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:29.150
has always been there because

00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:29.160
their

00:10:29.160 --> 00:10:30.950
mom and dad were in ministry, so

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:30.960
they

00:10:30.960 --> 00:10:32.790
just followed behind them

00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:35.910
and inherited what they had.

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:37.270
There's a big difference between being

00:10:37.280 --> 00:10:38.350
like a Billy Burke—being a

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:40.350
trailblazer

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:42.110
that is still going

00:10:42.120 --> 00:10:43.470
strong—and

00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:44.910
hearing some people that are

00:10:44.920 --> 00:10:46.150
parrots.

00:10:46.160 --> 00:10:48.630
I watch a lot of parrots;

00:10:48.640 --> 00:10:50.710
I watch the parrots. But where is

00:10:50.720 --> 00:10:52.830
it truly at in you

00:10:52.840 --> 00:10:55.270
when you say, "I

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:57.230
want revival"? I'm trying to

00:10:57.240 --> 00:10:59.550
challenge you right now

